"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-cycling-news-usa-cycling-announces-road-race-team-for-paris-that-will-try-to-end-40-year-olympic-medal-drought\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PLATEAU DES GLIERES, FRANCE - JUNE 09: Matteo Jorgenson of The United States and Team Visma | Lease a Bike - White Best Young Rider Jersey competes in the breakaway during the 76th Criterium du Dauphine 2024, Stage 9 a 160.6km stage from Thones to Plateau des Glieres 1444m / #UCIWT / on June 09, 2024 in Plateau des Glieres, France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 333, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 63, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999293205264466, \"rank\": 5.032807551863629e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Photo by Dario Belingheri/Getty Images)  Getty Images  Magnus Sheffield and Matteo Jorgenson will join Brandon McNulty on the U.S. cycling team for the Paris Olympics, giving the American contingent perhaps its best chance in four decades to win a road race medal.\", \"from\": 334, \"to\": 599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 376, \"end\": 381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999988329861924, \"rank\": 6.383430378132595e-07, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 390, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magnus_Sheffield\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Magnus Sheffield\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magnus_Sheffield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Magnus_Sheffield\"}, {\"begin\": 411, \"end\": 427, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matteo Jorgenson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matteo_Jorgenson\"}, {\"begin\": 438, \"end\": 453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McNulty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brandon McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McNulty\"}, {\"begin\": 514, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999681908077658, \"rank\": 3.0994830123493696e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McNulty had already qualified for the team by winning the national time trial championship earlier this year.\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 601, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.674250675750629e-13, \"text\": \"McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The big question was who would join him.\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 751, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"USA Cycling had to weigh which of its potential riders would be on the start line for the Tour de France on June 29, then pick the team best suited for the Olympic course that begins and ends in Paris.\", \"from\": 752, \"to\": 953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 752, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.492877308915744e-35, \"text\": \"USA Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Cycling\"}, {\"begin\": 842, \"end\": 856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999822319978748, \"rank\": 1.7768283767908195e-05, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 947, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1615682693177156e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The announcement came Friday, five weeks before the opening ceremony.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Going to the Olympics was one of my biggest goals growing up,\\\" Sheffield said.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am incredibly proud to represent the U.S. in Paris as well as all the people that have helped me along the way.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1154, \"end\": 1159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1615682693177156e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think it will fully sink in until I am there.\\\"\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Chloe Dygert and Taylor Knibb already had secured the two women's spots on the team.\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1290, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\", \"score\": 0.9999999166202577, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chloe Dygert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chlo\\u00e9_Dygert\"}, {\"begin\": 1295, \"end\": 1307, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taylor Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dygert won the time trial world title to earn an automatic nomination, while Knibb was a surprising winner of the U.S. time trial championship to earn her spot.\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1523, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1440, \"end\": 1445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"score\": 0.999999999906322, \"rank\": 9.345170290149899e-11, \"text\": \"Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both will be busy in Paris.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1546, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1615682693177156e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along with the road race and time trial, where Dygert will be heavily favored to win gold, she will be racing in the velodrome later in the Olympics as part of the U.S. pursuit squad.\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Knibb already had qualified for the Paris Games in the triathlon before making the cycling team; she finished 16th in the event at the Tokyo Games.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1884, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1737, \"end\": 1742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"score\": 0.999999999906322, \"rank\": 9.345170290149899e-11, \"text\": \"Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am very honored, grateful and excited for the opportunity to represent Team USA with USA Cycling,\\\" Knibb said.\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1988, \"end\": 1993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"score\": 0.999999999906322, \"rank\": 9.345170290149899e-11, \"text\": \"Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It would not have been possible without the support of my amazing family, friends, coaches, manager, sponsors and USA Triathlon.\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2115, \"end\": 2128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.541534205045115e-14, \"text\": \"USA Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Cycling has a very steep learning curve,\\\" she added, \\\"and I am simultaneously excited and nervous for what lies ahead.\\\"\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. has struggled in the road race since the 1984 Los Angeles Games, when Alexi Grewal won the men's race and Connie Carpenter and Rebecca Twig went one-two in the women's event.\", \"from\": 2253, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexi_Grewal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Alexi Grewal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexi_Grewal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alexi_Grewal\"}, {\"begin\": 2368, \"end\": 2374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Appleseed\", \"score\": 0.9942330548999124, \"rank\": 0.0022636491651947606, \"text\": \"Connie\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Appleseed\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johnny_Appleseed\"}, {\"begin\": 2389, \"end\": 2396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"score\": 0.9999856114535006, \"rank\": 1.4388753355497461e-05, \"text\": \"Rebecca\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rebecca_Napier\"}, {\"begin\": 2397, \"end\": 2401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twig\", \"score\": 0.9686540694495898, \"rank\": 0.03236029408116175, \"text\": \"Twig\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twig\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twig\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, European countries have dominated the medal table, though Richard Carapaz of Ecuador used a stunning attack to win a surprising gold in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2590, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2506, \"end\": 2521, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Richard Carapaz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\"}, {\"begin\": 2525, \"end\": 2532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"score\": 0.9755352487053748, \"rank\": 0.025021058792778966, \"text\": \"Ecuador\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ecuador\"}, {\"begin\": 2584, \"end\": 2589, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9425517281775881, \"rank\": 0.06061775877080795, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the UCI, which governs international cycling, changed its quota system for the Olympics in an attempt to achieve gender parity across all events.\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2600, \"end\": 2603, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCI_World_Tour\", \"score\": 0.9989833928784903, \"rank\": 0.0010176416633406874, \"text\": \"UCI\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCI_World_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UCI_World_Tour\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That means a much smaller number of riders in the men's race - 90 rather than the 130 that started in Tokyo - and that increases the possibility of a team such as the U.S. making a statement at the finish.\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2844, \"end\": 2849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9425517281775881, \"rank\": 0.06061775877080795, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McNulty nearly did in Tokyo anyway.\", \"from\": 2949, \"to\": 2984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2971, \"end\": 2976, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9425517281775881, \"rank\": 0.06061775877080795, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He attacked with Carapaz with about 15 miles (25 kilometers) left in the race, though he was unable to stay with him.\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3002, \"end\": 3009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carapaz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Carapaz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carapaz rode away from him with about three miles to go and McNulty wound up sixth.\", \"from\": 3103, \"to\": 3186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3163, \"end\": 3170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.674250675750629e-13, \"text\": \"McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That top result - sixth in the road race - just motivates me all the more,\\\" McNulty said.\", \"from\": 3188, \"to\": 3278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3265, \"end\": 3272, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.674250675750629e-13, \"text\": \"McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The race was super aggressive.\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3310, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I relive it all the time.\", \"from\": 3311, \"to\": 3336, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At home in Arizona and Girona, (Italy), I am already training with 100 percent focus on Paris.\\\"\", \"from\": 3337, \"to\": 3432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3348, \"end\": 3355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_Wildcats\", \"score\": 0.9983495312254486, \"rank\": 0.0009318396771641702, \"text\": \"Arizona\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_Wildcats\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arizona_Wildcats\"}, {\"begin\": 3360, \"end\": 3366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Girona\", \"score\": 0.9944021762315528, \"rank\": 0.005629328882064848, \"text\": \"Girona\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Girona\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Girona\"}, {\"begin\": 3369, \"end\": 3374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9949347848449516, \"rank\": 0.004947168109491194, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1615682693177156e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McNulty has had a strong season.\", \"from\": 3434, \"to\": 3466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3434, \"end\": 3441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.674250675750629e-13, \"text\": \"McNulty\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_McNulty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was the overall winner at a race in Spain, won time trial stages at the UAE Tour and the Tour de Romandie, and finished third overall at the prestigious Paris-Nice race that Jorgenson won.\", \"from\": 3467, \"to\": 3658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3506, \"end\": 3511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999976458130249, \"rank\": 2.3501523864376626e-06, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3542, \"end\": 3550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UAE_Tour\", \"score\": 0.7866058569390825, \"rank\": 0.2087101805370876, \"text\": \"UAE Tour\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UAE_Tour\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UAE_Tour\"}, {\"begin\": 3559, \"end\": 3575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Romandie\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.016643879158502e-22, \"text\": \"Tour de Romandie\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Romandie\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_Romandie\"}, {\"begin\": 3623, \"end\": 3633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Nice\", \"score\": 0.8313420322998837, \"rank\": 0.04320987654320691, \"text\": \"Paris-Nice\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Nice\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\\u2013Nice\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 22-year-old Sheffield is the least experienced rider on the U.S. squad but already has some big results to his name.\", \"from\": 3660, \"to\": 3780, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3676, \"end\": 3685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheffield\", \"score\": 0.9998916115064586, \"rank\": 0.00010793484842774225, \"text\": \"Sheffield\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheffield\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sheffield\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Two years ago, he won Brabantse Pijl, one of the major one-day races in Flanders - a first for an American in more than a decade.\", \"from\": 3781, \"to\": 3910, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3803, \"end\": 3817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brabantse_Pijl\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1445815606980164e-34, \"text\": \"Brabantse Pijl\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brabantse_Pijl\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brabantse_Pijl\"}, {\"begin\": 3879, \"end\": 3887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999681908077658, \"rank\": 3.0994830123493696e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jorgenson made a name for himself at last year's Tour de France, where he was active in several breakaways and nearly won atop Puy de D\\u00f4me.\", \"from\": 3912, \"to\": 4051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3961, \"end\": 3975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999822319978748, \"rank\": 1.7768283767908195e-05, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 4039, \"end\": 4050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puy_de_D\\u00f4me\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Puy de D\\u00f4me\", \"types\": [\"Q8502\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puy_de_D\\u00f4me\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Puy_de_D\\u00f4me\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 24-year-old has been even better this year, winning Dwars door Vlaanderen and finishing second at the Criterium du Dauphine against a field that included some of the biggest names in the sport.\", \"from\": 4052, \"to\": 4249, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4108, \"end\": 4129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1110505117292412e-22, \"text\": \"Dwars door Vlaanderen\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\", \"Q15091377\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\"}, {\"begin\": 4108, \"end\": 4129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dwars_door_Vlaanderen\", \"score\": 1.